Encode the given data/string to Morse Code

Input:   A file with data to be encoded.
Output:  A file called Output.txt is created at the current working directory which contains
         the Morse Code equivalent of the input file

Usage: 002MorseEncode.py [-h] --f FILEPATH 
Optional Arguments:
    -h, --help      Shows the help message and exits
    --f FILEPATH    Enter the file path

Example:
1: Have a file named input.txt in the current working directory
Command Line: 002-MorseEncode.py --f input.txt
2: Have a file named input.txt in C drive
Command Line: 002-MorseEncode.py --f C:\input.txt
